    "strings": [
      "CONFIDENTIAL",
      "Transportation Insurance Specialists",
      "David Reinhardt, Vice President",
      "03/15/2026",
      "RE: Great Lakes Freight Systems, Inc. \u2014 Transfer Submission",
      "1200 Nationwide Boulevard, Columbus, OH, 43215",
      "To: Underwriting Department, Standard Insurance Company",
      "Dear Underwriting Team,",
      "Account Overview",
      "We are pleased to submit ",
      "Great Lakes Freight Systems, Inc.",
      " for your review and consideration. The insured is a",
      "regional trucking and freight logistics \u2014 LTL and FTL general freight, warehousing and distribution services across",
      "the Midwest and Mid-Atlantic corridors, headquartered in Columbus, with approximately 38 years of operating",
      "history. Coverage is requested for Workers' Compensation, General Liability, Commercial Auto, Commercial",
      "Property, Umbrella / Excess, Motor Truck Cargo.",
      "Coverage Requested",
      "Workers' Compensation:",
      " Workers' Compensation \u2014 statutory limits with employer's liability of $1M/$1M/$1M.",
      "Workers' Compensation coverage is provided through Ohio Bureau of Workers' Compensation per state statute.",
      "General Liability:",
      " General Liability coverage is requested on an occurrence form with $2,000,000.00 per",
      "occurrence and $4,000,000.00 aggregate, including standard premises/operations and products/completed",
      "operations.",
      "Commercial Auto:",
      " Business Auto with combined single limit of $5,000,000.00, covering all owned, hired, and",
      "non-owned vehicles.",
      "Commercial Property:",
      " Commercial Property coverage for all scheduled locations on a special form with",
      "replacement cost valuation.",
      "Umbrella / Excess:",
      " Commercial Umbrella with a $10,000,000.00 occurrence/$10,000,000.00 aggregate limit,",
      "following form over primary GL, Auto, and Employer's Liability.",
      "Motor Truck Cargo:",
      " Motor Truck Cargo coverage as per expiring program.",
      "Loss History Summary",
      "The loss experience reflects a mixed trend with some large individual claims in the review period. Over the review",
      "period, the insured has incurred ",
      "48",
      " total claims with ",
      "$1,378,733.13",
      " in total paid losses and ",
      "$1,503,069.19",
      " total",
      "incurred. Currently, ",
      "10",
      " claims remain open and ",
      "38",
      " have been closed.",
      "Annualized loss ratio is ",
      "12.9%",
      " (avg annual incurred $300,613.84 against current annual premium $2,333,947.33",
      "over 5 loss years).",
      "Breakdown by coverage line:",
      "\u2022 ",
      " 24 claims, $826,622.56 paid, $888,785.06 incurred",
      " 5 claims, $54,126.51 paid, $54,126.51 incurred",
      " 16 claims, $387,376.46 paid, $449,550.02 incurred",
      " 2 claims, $106,691.36 paid, $106,691.36 incurred",
      " 0 claims, $0.00 paid, $0.00 incurred",
      " 1 claim, $3,916.24 paid, $3,916.24 incurred",
      "Risk Highlights",
      "\u2022 The insured maintains a formal business continuity and disaster recovery plan tested annually.",
      "\u2022 The insured maintains a dedicated safety committee that meets monthly and conducts quarterly site audits.",
      "\u2022 An employee assistance program and workplace wellness initiative have been in place for over five years.",
      "\u2022 The insured carries contractual risk transfer provisions in all subcontractor and vendor agreements.",
      "\u2022 A third-party risk control survey was completed within the past 12 months with favorable results.",
      "\u2022 The insured has implemented a formal return-to-work program that has reduced lost-time claims by over 30%.",
      "\u2022 All locations are equipped with security camera systems and 24/7 monitoring services.",
      "\u2022 With 485 employees and a structured HR program, the insured maintains low turnover and consistent safety",
      "training.",
      "\u2022 The insured's fleet of 37 vehicles is maintained under a documented preventive maintenance schedule.",
      "Broker Recommendation",
      "Given the favorable loss history and proactive risk management, we encourage competitive pricing for this submission.",
      "Please do not hesitate to contact us with any questions or if additional information is required.",
      "Respectfully submitted,",
      "David Reinhardt",
      "Vice President",
      "Page 1 of 2",
      "Page 2 of 2",
      "M. Johnson",
      "6/18/2025",
      "Need docs"
    ],
